Hi John,

I'm Priya
<https://novaforge-ai.qmailroute.net/x/d?c=61581159&l=e18481e7-4f1e-5330-a4ef-d78617cfd6d0&r=8ad34623-9efb-5fbd-a433-c09e7fc393gc>
from NovaForge
<https://novaforge-ai.qmailroute.net/x/d?c=61581159&l=7872de56-96d7-5a2d-cf57-d3a02fe03f1c&r=8ad34623-9efb-5fbd-a433-c09e7fc393gc>,
a research lab based in Toronto and San Francisco building the first
enterprise world model.

We recently tested frontier LLMs such as Claude and GPT on an agent
interface for Roller Coaster Tycoon 2 (everyone's favourite childhood
game!) that we built. We're publishing our research findings this Monday,
March 30th at 12:00 PM ET, and I'd love your help amplifying them.

Here's why we did it: frontier LLMs are topping the ARC-AGI leaderboard
<https://novaforge-ai.qmailroute.net/x/d?c=61581159&l=c16f7987-556c-5c4e-ccb4-9e9a52191bdd&r=8ad34623-9efb-5fbd-a433-c09e7fc393gc>,
but we wanted to know if that same intelligence holds up in a real
simulated business environment. So we built a recursive REPL agent, gave it
access to an OpenRCT2 API, and tested whether they could succeed.

Given your interest in AI and games, I thought you might find this worth
sharing. If you're able to repost our launch tweet, just reply "yes" by
Friday, March 27th and I'll send you the link the morning we go live.

Thanks for considering it!

Priya
NovaForge AI

